Yes — I can **read/search** your Gmail (I can’t send email or change anything).

I searched your inbox for **“Jia Hua / Jiahua / Chia Jia Hua”** plus **wedding / invitation / RSVP / save the date / 婚礼 / 婚宴 / 囍**, and also checked your Google Calendar for events containing **“Jia Hua/Jiahua”** and **“wedding”**.

### What I found
None of the emails that match **Jia Hua / chiajiahua@hotmail.com** contain a wedding date. The relevant hits were things like:
- **“AQ Practice (22-May)”** (attachment; no wedding info) — [Open in Gmail](https://mail.google.com/mail/#all/1798df58787f3ab8)
- Google Drive folder share invites where Jia Hua is included — [Open in Gmail](https://mail.google.com/mail/#all/179832a02c0d2420), [Open in Gmail](https://mail.google.com/mail/#all/179b806f6b134d89)

On Calendar, “wedding” finds a *different* wedding, and “Jia Hua/Jiahua” only finds old tuition/help events—no wedding entry.

### Most likely explanation
Jia Hua’s wedding details probably **aren’t in Gmail/Calendar** (could be WhatsApp/Telegram, a physical invite, a different email account, or an attached image/PDF I didn’t hit with keywords).

### Quick next moves (high-yield)
If you want, tell me **Jia Hua’s spouse/partner name** or the **venue name** (or even just a single keyword you remember from the invite), and I’ll re-search Gmail/Calendar using those.
